The paper deals with the formal verification of compilers, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The paper also deals with programming languages and compilers, which suggests that it may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper's focus on security benefits suggests that it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of formal methods and proof techniques suggests that it may belong to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
